{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Another summarization approach [55] which summarizes transaction datasets of network traffic into a compact version uses the frequent itemsets generated from the apriori algorithm.Owing to the shortcomings in applying traditional Apriori algorithms to bulk data, recently, many researchers have focused on refinements to improve the effectiveness of ARM.",
    "The novel algorithm, FEM (FP-growth & Eclat Mining) [45] which utilizes both FP-tree (Frequent-Pattern tree) and TIDlist (Transaction ID list) data structures have proven their efficiency in mining short and long patterns from both sparse and dense datasets.",
    "Another study presented in [48] deviated from traditional ARM algorithms and presented a fuzzy extended Boolean framework for identifying association rules in a text document and used the generated rules for query refinement in Information Retrieval.",
    "The DCI CLOSED [50], which is a novel and scalable algorithm based on the divide-and-conquer approach has been used to mine closed frequent itemsets using the bitwise vertical representation of the database.",
    "Apriori MSG-P [53] is another modified version of the traditional Apriori algorithm for discovering hidden information in ARM which has proven its efficiency using an operational database at a hospital."
  ],
